  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-04-19",
    "date": "2024-03-27T18:08:34Z",
    "text": "Providing Child Care for Police Officers Act of 2023 \n\nThis bill directs the Department of Health and Human Services to establish a grant pilot program for child care services for the children of law enforcement officers. Grants are provided to eligible states to provide assistance to a law enforcement agency or a group of entities to establish and operate child care programs for the minor children of law enforcement officers during shift work and abnormal work hours."
